# Quick Oatmeal Pancakes

![Quick Oatmeal Pancakes](https://images.media-allrecipes.com/userphotos/560x315/3850418.jpg)

## Ingredients:
- 1 cup quick-cooking oats
- 1 1/4 cups milk
- 1/2 cup all-purpose flour
- 2 tablespoons brown sugar
- 1 tablespoon baking powder
- 1/2 teaspoon salt
- 1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon
- 2 eggs
- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1/4 cup vegetable oil

## Instructions:
1. In a small bowl, combine oats and milk; let stand for 5 minutes.
2. In a large bowl, combine the flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, and cinnamon.
3. Stir the eggs, vanilla, and oil into the oat mixture; add to the dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
4. Pour batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto a hot greased griddle; turn when bubbles form on top.
5. Cook until the second side is golden brown.

Enjoy your quick oatmeal pancakes!

Recipe Source: [AllRecipes](https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/228654/quick-oatmeal-pancakes/)
